*   **Data-Hypothesis Alignment**: The proposal claims to bypass the "super-resolution bottleneck" of Planck beams (4.4'–4.7') using CIB-tSZ cross-correlation. However, the CIB maps at these frequencies are also smoothed by these same large beams. The model cannot recover sub-arcminute tSZ features from CIB data that lacks that spatial resolution without relying on "hallucinated" priors, which the loss function explicitly tries to prevent.
