*   **Physical Reality**: The proposal assumes the CIB acts as a "physical prior." In reality, the CIB is a projection of high-redshift star formation, while tSZ is a line-of-sight integral of pressure. Their spatial correlation is significant but not deterministic. Relying on this correlation to "constrain" tSZ recovery is physically risky and may introduce systematic biases in the inferred gas pressure profiles.

**Strategic Pivot**: Abandon the "joint posterior" ambition. Instead, focus on a **Super-Resolution Denoising Autoencoder (SR-DAE)** that uses the multi-frequency CIB maps as *auxiliary input features* to guide the deconvolution of the SO-band maps. Use the ground-truth tSZ maps to train a supervised model to predict the high-resolution tSZ signal, using the `utils.powers` function as a spectral regularizer to ensure the model does not violate the known power spectrum of the FLAMINGO gas distribution.
